title: fanoutqa: List the top 5 fastest animals and their species. (0502dd01fd5bd124)

chat_history.content: List the top 5 fastest animals and their species.

Here are the top five fastest animals in the world by their top speed, along with their species:

1. Peregrine Falcon (*Falco peregrinus*): 389 km/h (242 mph) during a dive.
2. Golden Eagle (*Aquila chrysaetos*): 320 km/h (199 mph) during a dive.
3. White-throated Needletail (*Hirundapus caudacutus*): 170 km/h (105 mph) during level flight.
4. Eurasian Hobby (*Falco subbuteo*): 160 km/h (100 mph) during a dive.
5. Mexican Free-tailed Bat (*Tadarida brasiliensis*): 160 km/h (100 mph) during flight.

Note that the speeds mentioned above are the maximum speeds recorded for these animals. The speeds during level flight differ from the speeds during a dive, and some of the animals on this list achieve their highest speeds during a hunting dive.

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.
